        {
          "company": "Majesco (Acquired Vitech System)",
          "description": "\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003eEnhanced Core Administration functionality for the Vitech Velocity platform using Java, Spring Boot, and GWT, delivering robust enterprise-grade solutions.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eArchitected the migration of a mission-critical Document Generation module from a legacy monolith to a standalone microservice using the Strangler Fig Pattern.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eDecoupled complex document logic into a scalable, API-driven service, significantly improving fault isolation and reducing the need for extensive regression testing.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eOptimized system performance by deploying services to AWS with auto-scaling capabilities, ensuring stability during peak-hour bulk operations.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eReduced processing latency by integrating Redis as a distributed caching layer for high-frequency template metadata and document schemas.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eEngineered RESTful APIs to expose core functionality, streamlining integration with existing system and process APIs while simplifying production bug triage.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003ePioneered high-quality code standards by enforcing Test-Driven Development (TDD) using JUnit and Mockito, ensuring 100% test coverage for new implementations.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eCollaborated in a high-velocity Agile environment with 16-day sprints, consistently meeting delivery deadlines for the Enterprise Enablers Team.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eMaintained system integrity by performing root-cause analysis and resolving critical bugs within the Core Administration codebase.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e",
          "hidden": false,
